# Code Quality

## Style

- async/await for asynchronous operations
- JSDoc on public methods
- Use `this.log.*` / adapter logging — never `console.log` in production code
- Tabs, double quotes (see `prettier.config.mjs`)
- ESLint via `@iobroker/eslint-config` (`eslint.config.mjs`) — run `npm run lint` after every change; CI treats warnings as errors (`--max-warnings 0`)

## Resource cleanup

Stop polling, timers, and intervals in `onUnload()`; always call `callback()`:

```javascript
onUnload(callback) {
  try {
    if (this.pollTimer) clearTimeout(this.pollTimer);
    if (this.versionTimer) clearInterval(this.versionTimer);
    Object.values(this.resetTimers || {}).forEach(timer => {
      if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);
    });
    callback();
  } catch {
    callback();
  }
}
```

## Error handling

- Wrap async/API work in try/catch; log errors, do not crash the adapter
- Use adapter log levels: error, warn, info, debug
- Handle network failures gracefully; set `online` state to `false` and traffic light to red
- Do not retry failed API calls in a tight loop — wait for the next poll cycle

## HTTP

- **Preferred:** native `node:http` via `lib/httpHelper.js`
- **Avoid:** axios, request, or other HTTP libraries

## Dependencies

- Use `npm ci` in CI; commit `package-lock.json` with `package.json`
- Use `@iobroker/adapter-core`; avoid deprecated packages
- Update dependencies in separate PRs only
- Prefer built-in Node.js modules where possible
